AGOP Comments on Issues; Wants
Equal Chance for Success for All
. By Phil Johnson
No man's freedom is secure
until all men are free. The goal
of the members of the republic
can Party is to bring equal opportunity to every man. Not
every man jul succeed in all
of his limitations in life, but
his success Or failure should
be the result of his personal
facilities as a man, not of a
impressive social system, of
legal restrictions, of a lack of
educational opportunities, or of
object poverty. ~
Civil rights is the most urgent
issue in our domestic life. All
forms of racial discrimination
must be destroyed. Each indi»
visual Is entitled to equal treaty
ment by all other Americans,
whether by government officials or by other citizens. He
should be able to vote, live
where he choices, worklwherr
ever he is qualified, and use
any public facility on the same
basis as any other citizen.
The circle of poverty and
insurance which kinds so many
fellow Americans must be broken, Educational opportunities
must be provided to the capable but poor, Training and
placement aid must be extended
to those who do not presently
have the skills to participate
in modern industry. expressed
areas must be helped back on
their feet, to enable them to
make positive contributions to
the nation.
Wherever possible, these matters should be dealt with by
local or state governments,
since the federal government is
notoriously inefficient and incredible in operation. However
some states have refused to assume th e i r responsibilities.
Some have themselves actively
isolated the principles of equality which are the strength of our
society. In these cases, there is
no alternative but federal ace
lion,
 
 
In foreign policy, similar
principles apply. The developing nations should be added in
reaching economic and political
growth and stability, to the
end that they will become
sound and autonomous citizens
of the world community.
communist, as it Is price
tired by the Soviet blog, is a
direct hypothesis of all principles of freedom, both for individuals and for nations. It
must be register actively on all
prints.
Government itself must be
turned of the corruption re
sealed by the standard of this
administration. The relationships and obstructionists now
controlling the Democratic
Congressional machine should
be replaced by men various to
serve the nation and the principles of equality which give it
strength.
It is to this end that the Republican Party is dedicated in
1964.
 
