The votes cannon expect to
agree with a candidate's total
philosophy, only with his monitor
cal philosophy. Moreover, a
vote for a candidate does not
necessarily enlarge his entire
political position, only his basic
political principles, Principles
are important, for it is only in
terms of principles that a candidate can offer us a program
and indicate his future course,
not by floating instructions and
contradictory promises about
a miscellaneous Collection of
concrete, short-term issues.
Views on whether the United
States should or should not
withdraw from the United Nations are not principles; views
on whether a nation should or
should not protect its governments are printer1e5#principles that cover many issues
besides the U, N.
Thus, a principle is an instruction which subsumes a
great number of completed. It
is only by means oi principles
that men can judge the alternatives contracting them and project their future. If a candidate does not integrate pieces
meal goals into conceptual
terms, but rather products his
campaign in terms of completed, he requests the voters
to hand him a blank check for
power. If a candidate grades,
equivocates and sides his stand
under a junkrheap oi random
completed, it is impossible to
predict his future course of action.
With this as a standard, it is
easy to see why Senator Barry ,
polyester is the best candidate
in the field today. The major
difference between
and his opponents is this: They
believe that some elements of
