conscious Vice President ti Dangerous luxury for Present,
robert Humphrey Offers Necessary Experience, treatment
By Dennis Murphy
Neither the Republicans nor
the Democrats can longer afford the luxury of nomination
for Vice President conscious
candidates whose sole purpose
is to balance the ticket geoA
graphically, automatically, or
religiously. The man nominated
for Democratic VicevPresidential Candidate must possess all
the ability, experience, and confidence required by the office
of President — and he must
show promise of becoming a
truly great President. It is our
concern belief that Senator Hu—
best Humphrey of Minnesota
shows that promise.
Senator Humphrey holds no
claim to striking good looks;
he does not represent a fabulous northeastern State, Humphrey is, instead, one of the
most residential men in Washington; he is a Liberal without
reservations whose record of
progressive legislation dates
back to his first election office,
“I believe in the liberalism of
advocacy and action," related
Humphrey in an article for the
Phi Beta happy Journal. Liberalism should be related with
“Man’s striking for Civilization
and density." It is a . . philosophy willing to use the state
to achieve freedom."
Few modern political figures
have a record of accomplishments to compare with that of
