nov. Romney Is Candidate lo Cope
With Problems. rangers of 60's
By Ken coleman
The Republican Party must
choose as its Presidential candidate for 1964 a man who has
proved that he has the ability
to cope with the problems of
the 1960's, and a man Who
recognized the rangers which
are interest in big government,
big business, and big unions.
Such a man is George Romney,
the Governor of Michigan.
In 1962 Romney ended a 14
year Democratic dynamic on
the Michigan state-house by depending the Democratic incorrect by over 78,000 votes. After
only one year in office Romney
had wired out the state’s massive 85.6 million deficit.
Earlier he had shown the
same carrier of ability in industry. When he was selected
as President of American
Motors Corporation, that firm
was on the verse of collapse.
When he left American Motors
to run for Governor in 1962
that firm had become established as one of the most vital
and stable in the automotive
industry.
It was Romney who introduced both the concept and
term of “compact” cars to the
American automotive industry.
Romney firmly believes that
there should he more citizen
participation in government. As
Governor .he has set aside
Thursday earnings to allow
any citizen to come in and discuss problems. Romney has
said that America respiratory
needs a party that is respective
to the people.
On Civil Rights Romney has
stated time and again his opposition to “discrimination of
any kind." He has ,customized
President Johnson’s tax pro-
IOMNEY
gray as a trick saying the deficit will continue at the same '
level.
Romney says that American
foreign policy must adopt a
new outlook. He says that the
policy of the present administration has led to the position
where freedom is in retreat all
over the world.
The Republicans can do no
less than navigate the person
who Margaret Chase Smith has
described as the man who is
“probably the most ideal candy—
date in the party." That man
is Governor George Romney
of Michigan.
 
